<TITLE> Over 2000 police convicted of crimes in 2 years </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 15 (bdnews24.com)Over 2000 police personnel were found guilty of different crimes in the last two years, home minister Sahara Khantun told parliament Monday. Replying to a question from Jatiya Party MP Salma Islam, the minister said the government handed down 2,056 policemen different punishments including termination from service, suspension, forced retirement, salary reduction, demotion, and others. Police authorities received different complaints of corruption, misconduct, breach of discipline and other offences against them. The minister also said, "Besides, 1,224 police personnel were given heavy punishments while 12,891 got light punishments in 2008. "In 2009, 1,115 policemen got heavy punishments and 12,408 were awarded with light punishments," Sahara said. There are about 1 lakh 16 thousand police personnel in Bangladesh, according to the police headquarters.
